1
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:11,320
When the wind blows,

2
00:02:11,760 --> 00:02:13,320
it's time to travel far.

3
00:02:14,320 --> 00:02:15,520
The lighter the leaf,

4
00:02:15,880 --> 00:02:17,480
the further it will be blown.

5
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:26,680
Cencen.

6
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:27,640
Mom.

7
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:30,530
Let's go.

8
00:02:37,680 --> 00:02:38,240
Sis.

9
00:02:39,600 --> 00:02:40,720
I miss you so much.

10
00:02:40,840 --> 00:02:41,770
Long time no see.

11
00:02:43,440 --> 00:02:44,970
I think you've lost weight.

12
00:02:45,160 --> 00:02:46,120
I'm on a diet.

13
00:02:46,160 --> 00:02:47,320
Looking good, right?

14
00:02:47,320 --> 00:02:47,980
Oh, really.

15
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,060
Say hi to your aunt.

16
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:49,930
Hello, Aunt.

17
00:02:50,640 --> 00:02:52,640
Xiaocen, you're getting prettier.

18
00:02:53,760 --> 00:02:54,690
Thank you, Aunt.

19
00:02:55,079 --> 00:02:55,800
All right, let's go.

20
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:56,079
Let's go.

21
00:02:56,079 --> 00:02:57,160
Come, let me help you with your luggage.

22
00:02:57,160 --> 00:02:57,920
No need, Aunt. I can do it myself.

23
00:02:57,920 --> 00:02:58,520
It's fine.

24
00:02:58,600 --> 00:02:59,680
I'll help you with your luggage.

25
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:00,210
Let's go.

26
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,000
Come here, Cencen.

27
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,460
Take your medicine first.

28
00:03:07,320 --> 00:03:07,840
Sis.

29
00:03:08,440 --> 00:03:11,000
Sorry to trouble you for the years we'll be here.

30
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:12,930
We're family. No need to be polite.

31
00:03:13,240 --> 00:03:13,880
Actually, sis,

32
00:03:13,880 --> 00:03:15,210
you didn't have to come.

33
00:03:15,240 --> 00:03:16,760
Since Xiaocen is studying in Jingdezhen,

34
00:03:16,760 --> 00:03:18,890
I'll definitely take good care of her.

35
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:22,400
You know Xiaocen's condition.

36
00:03:23,320 --> 00:03:25,160
She's been in poor health since she was little,

37
00:03:25,160 --> 00:03:26,760
and has hardly traveled far.

38
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:29,360
Now she got into a university in Jingdezhen.

39
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:30,820
So I accompanied her here.

40
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:41,370
Are you hot, sister?

41
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:42,840
Yes. Why is it so hot?

42
00:03:42,920 --> 00:03:44,120
Come in. It's cool inside.

43
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:45,160
Here, give it to me.

44
00:03:45,160 --> 00:03:45,820
Let me do it.

45
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:46,840
I got it.

46
00:03:49,720 --> 00:03:50,360
Xiaoxing.

47
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:51,960
Sister,

48
00:03:53,440 --> 00:03:54,370
long time no see.

49
00:03:54,480 --> 00:03:54,880
Sister,

50
00:03:54,880 --> 00:03:56,680
I've already set up your room for you.

51
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:57,360
Xiaoxing,

52
00:03:57,360 --> 00:03:58,440
why didn't you greet your aunt?

53
00:03:58,440 --> 00:03:59,440
That's impolite.

54
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:05,400
No need.

55
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:06,850
Just stand right there.

56
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:10,340
How are you?

57
00:04:10,600 --> 00:04:11,930
Are you feeling unwell?

58
00:04:12,280 --> 00:04:12,840
No.

59
00:04:13,240 --> 00:04:14,320
I'm okay.

60
00:04:14,760 --> 00:04:15,880
Give me the pillow.

61
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:19,079
Alright.

62
00:04:20,959 --> 00:04:22,600
I'll go help your aunt cook.

63
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:23,600
You tidy up first.

64
00:04:23,840 --> 00:04:24,360
Okay.

65
00:04:24,960 --> 00:04:25,760
Qingying.

66
00:04:47,760 --> 00:04:49,240
Driver, stop right here.

67
00:04:50,760 --> 00:04:51,420
We're here.

68
00:04:53,320 --> 00:04:54,980
It's so nice without traffic.

69
00:04:55,280 --> 00:04:56,740
Come on, Xiaocen. Get out.

70
00:04:57,840 --> 00:04:59,370
Take your time getting out.

71
00:05:02,360 --> 00:05:04,520
Watch out for cars when you cross the street here.

72
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:06,160
Your school is right across the street.

73
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:06,760
Thank you.

74
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:11,040
I have to say,

75
00:05:11,040 --> 00:05:12,360
this school is quite large.

76
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:12,960
Right?

77
00:05:13,040 --> 00:05:13,880
It's really nice.

78
00:05:13,880 --> 00:05:14,640
I didn't expect this.

79
00:05:14,640 --> 00:05:16,040
There are so many people.

80
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:17,300
It's quite lively.

81
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:19,240
There's a river nearby too.

82
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:19,640
Yeah.

83
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:20,120
Indeed.

84
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:22,440
There are quite a few clubs at your school.

85
00:05:22,440 --> 00:05:24,100
Yes. Look, there are several.

86
00:05:24,840 --> 00:05:26,360
Xiaocen, do you want to take a look?

87
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:27,240
No need.

88
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:29,520
Joining clubs is a waste of time.

89
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:31,120
Focus on your main courses first.

90
00:05:31,120 --> 00:05:32,080
We can talk about that later.

91
00:05:32,080 --> 00:05:32,610
Let's go.

92
00:05:33,120 --> 00:05:34,040
Come on.

93
00:05:39,960 --> 00:05:40,560
Xiaocen.

94
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:42,960
There are lots of snack shops in the north.

95
00:05:42,960 --> 00:05:44,159
I heard they are quite good.

96
00:05:44,159 --> 00:05:45,920
You can try them when you're free.

97
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:47,240
What are you talking about?

98
00:05:47,240 --> 00:05:49,080
The food there is the most unhygienic.

99
00:05:49,080 --> 00:05:49,960
Mom, Auntie,

100
00:05:50,280 --> 00:05:51,340
I'll get going now.

101
00:05:52,400 --> 00:05:54,200
Did you forget something again?

102
00:05:57,400 --> 00:05:58,440
Did you set the alarm for your medicine?

103
00:05:58,440 --> 00:05:59,440
I set it.

104
00:05:59,680 --> 00:06:00,880
Okay. Don't forget.

105
00:06:02,040 --> 00:06:03,500
I'm leaving. Auntie, Mom.

106
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:04,080
Bye.

107
00:06:04,120 --> 00:06:04,640
Bye.

108
00:06:04,920 --> 00:06:05,450
Go ahead.

109
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:11,440
How do I wear this?

110
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:12,560
Just loop it in.

111
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:13,960
I received that book.

112
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:15,000
It's pretty good.

113
00:06:15,360 --> 00:06:15,760
Right?

114
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:16,960
How much is it?

115
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:17,680
Look.

116
00:06:18,280 --> 00:06:18,720
Here.

117
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:19,920
Let me scan your code.

118
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:20,250
Okay.

119
00:06:22,960 --> 00:06:23,560
Hello.

120
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:25,740
Is this seat taken?

121
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:27,060
It's taken. Sorry.

122
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:31,560
I'll go sit over there.

123
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:32,320
This is it.

124
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:36,000
Let me play a round.

125
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:36,360
Sure.

126
00:06:37,840 --> 00:06:38,560
Yan Xue.

127
00:06:39,640 --> 00:06:41,300
Wait, Yuexin is sitting here.

128
00:06:41,760 --> 00:06:43,090
Then where should I sit?

129
00:06:43,120 --> 00:06:44,080
You can sit anywhere.

130
00:06:44,080 --> 00:06:45,940
Seats haven't been assigned yet.

131
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:48,080
Hello. Can I sit with you?

132
00:06:49,440 --> 00:06:50,159
Sure.

133
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:55,760
Thank you.

134
00:07:01,280 --> 00:07:03,010
Did you smell something weird?

135
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:09,120
No, I didn't.

136
00:07:10,080 --> 00:07:11,210
Did I smell it wrong?

137
00:07:11,440 --> 00:07:12,280
You choose him.

138
00:07:12,280 --> 00:07:12,920
Right?

139
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:29,090
This looks good.

140
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:54,240
Okay.

141
00:07:55,080 --> 00:07:56,740
Everyone, please quiet down.

142
00:07:56,760 --> 00:07:58,280
I am your homeroom teacher.

143
00:07:58,280 --> 00:07:59,240
Now, let's

144
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:00,650
do something together.

145
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:09,720
Sitting in a circle

146
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:10,880
makes you feel less nervous, right?

147
00:08:10,880 --> 00:08:12,040
My name is Liang Yiqing.

148
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:13,520
In the days to come,

149
00:08:13,520 --> 00:08:14,360
I will be

150
00:08:14,360 --> 00:08:14,760
your teacher

151
00:08:14,760 --> 00:08:16,120
for Introduction to Museology,

152
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:17,360
as well as your homeroom teacher.

153
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:18,000
So,

154
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,840
whether in your studies

155
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,060
or your daily life,

156
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:23,160
if you have any problems or difficulties,

157
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:24,360
you can always come to me.

158
00:08:24,360 --> 00:08:24,720
Okay.

159
00:08:24,720 --> 00:08:25,250
Alright.

160
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:27,520
Well, you all know me now.

161
00:08:27,520 --> 00:08:29,080
Now it's my turn to know you.

162
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:30,200
Let's start

163
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:31,040
with you.

164
00:08:31,040 --> 00:08:31,640
Sure.

165
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:34,000
Hello everyone, I'm Wang Lin.

166
00:08:34,159 --> 00:08:35,400
I'm from Fuyang, Anhui.

167
00:08:35,400 --> 00:08:36,039
I really like archaeology.

168
00:08:36,039 --> 00:08:36,799
We are from the same hometown.

169
00:08:36,799 --> 00:08:38,480
Hello, everyone. My name is Li Zhuoting.

170
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:39,400
My name is Xiaoyi.

171
00:08:39,400 --> 00:08:40,559
I am Wu Jing.

172
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:41,799
My name is Yan Xue.

173
00:08:41,799 --> 00:08:43,159
I really, really, really

174
00:08:43,159 --> 00:08:44,080
really like porcelain.

175
00:08:44,080 --> 00:08:45,960
I usually like watching Korean and Japanese variety shows,

176
00:08:45,960 --> 00:08:47,160
and I also pay attention to domestic entertainment.

177
00:08:47,160 --> 00:08:48,200
Skateboarding, skiing, ice skating.

178
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:49,760
High jump, long jump, jump rope.

179
00:08:49,760 --> 00:08:51,560
Just ask me if you need anything.

180
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:53,320
I have dozens of exclusive

181
00:08:53,320 --> 00:08:54,780
PDFs of celebrity gossip.

182
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:55,880
Anyone who needs it

183
00:08:55,880 --> 00:08:57,680
can ask me for the cloud drive link anytime.

184
00:08:57,680 --> 00:08:59,560
If you want to play murder mystery games or escape rooms,

185
00:08:59,560 --> 00:09:00,690
remember to ping me.

186
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:04,170
My name is Liang Juntao.

187
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:05,600
And I'm from Jiangxi.

188
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:09,130
Hello everyone, my name is Xu Xiao.

189
00:09:09,760 --> 00:09:10,890
Nice to meet you all.

190
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:11,800
Thank you.

191
00:09:13,760 --> 00:09:15,040
Xu Xiao is concise.

192
00:09:15,040 --> 00:09:16,360
Good. Very good.

193
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:17,320
Next student.

194
00:09:17,320 --> 00:09:18,840
Hello everyone, my name is Zhou Kai.

195
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:20,320
Hello everyone, my name is Li Kun,

196
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:21,180
from Shandong.

197
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:23,080
People there are honest.

198
00:09:23,080 --> 00:09:24,340
I love eating noodles.

199
00:09:25,080 --> 00:09:26,120
Yes.

200
00:09:26,360 --> 00:09:27,000
Hello everyone.

201
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:28,800
My name is Zhao Chen, from Hebei.

202
00:09:28,840 --> 00:09:30,120
So close, so beautiful.

203
00:09:30,120 --> 00:09:31,240
Visit Hebei on weekends.

204
00:09:31,240 --> 00:09:33,040
Welcome to visit Hebei.

205
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:33,600
Next

206
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:34,960
student, please.

207
00:09:36,960 --> 00:09:38,880
Hello everyone, my name is Zhao Xiaocen.

208
00:09:38,880 --> 00:09:40,280
'Zhao' as in Zhao Yun.

209
00:09:40,440 --> 00:09:42,840
And 'Cen' as in Master Cen and Dan Qiusheng.

210
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:44,800
I don't know if you guys have taken

211
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:45,760
the MBTI test.

212
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:48,720
I am an INFP.

213
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:50,680
So when you meet me for the first time,

214
00:09:50,680 --> 00:09:52,960
I might seem a bit nervous and quiet.

215
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:54,000
But deep down,

216
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:56,160
I really hope to make friends with everyone.

217
00:09:56,160 --> 00:09:57,440
I am a good listener.

218
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:59,400
So if you have any troubles, you can come to me.

219
00:09:59,400 --> 00:10:00,360
I want to be your friend.

220
00:10:00,360 --> 00:10:01,960
Then I will come to you often.

221
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:03,680
Good.

222
00:10:04,240 --> 00:10:04,840
Very good.

223
00:10:05,960 --> 00:10:08,160
Great. I really need a friend like that.

224
00:10:11,280 --> 00:10:13,200
Okay, next student, please.

225
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:15,680
Hello, everyone. I'm Lin Yuexin.

226
00:10:15,680 --> 00:10:16,880
I wonder if you guys have ever taken

227
00:10:16,880 --> 00:10:17,800
the MBTI test.

228
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:20,360
As for me, I'm an ENFJ, the Protagonist.

229
00:10:20,640 --> 00:10:21,680
I am an extrovert

230
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:22,840
and I like to communicate with everyone.

231
00:10:22,840 --> 00:10:24,840
I am someone who likes to help classmates.

232
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:26,320
If you have any questions,

233
00:10:26,400 --> 00:10:27,680
you can always come to me.

234
00:10:27,680 --> 00:10:28,400
I'm the same as you.

235
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:29,080
Really?

236
00:10:29,160 --> 00:10:29,760
Really!

237
00:10:29,800 --> 00:10:30,600
Mr. Liang, we're on the same wavelength.

238
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:32,000
I'm an ENTJ (Commander).

239
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:33,600
I'm an ENTJ (Commander).

240
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:33,960
How about you?

241
00:10:33,960 --> 00:10:34,440
Me too.

242
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:36,480
You too?

243
00:10:36,520 --> 00:10:37,200
We're the same.

244
00:10:37,200 --> 00:10:38,240
Where is it? Let me take a look too.

245
00:10:38,240 --> 00:10:39,840
This one, this one, this one.

246
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:42,280
Class, class.

247
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:43,360
This topic,

248
00:10:43,400 --> 00:10:45,040
if we keep talking about it,

249
00:10:45,040 --> 00:10:46,960
we'll probably talk until dark.

250
00:10:47,160 --> 00:10:49,220
All right, let's stop here for today.

251
00:10:49,720 --> 00:10:50,320
You there.

252
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:51,560
Me?

253
00:10:59,160 --> 00:11:00,160
Hello, everyone.

254
00:11:03,640 --> 00:11:04,400
My name is...

255
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:07,130
My name is Zhao Xiaocen.

256
00:11:16,760 --> 00:11:17,400
Sir.

257
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:20,960
I don't really know what to say.

258
00:11:21,800 --> 00:11:23,520
Xiaocen might be a bit nervous.

259
00:11:23,520 --> 00:11:25,450
Let's give her a round of applause.

260
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:31,520
I...

261
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:32,320
I...

262
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:38,530
It's okay, Xiaocen.

263
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:40,560
You're probably too nervous today.

264
00:11:40,560 --> 00:11:41,720
We can get to know each other later.

265
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:42,780
Please take a seat.

266
00:11:48,280 --> 00:11:49,340
It's finally over.

267
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:52,800
Don't forget about tonight.

268
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:53,760
The whole class is going.

269
00:11:53,760 --> 00:11:54,160
Okay.

270
00:11:54,560 --> 00:11:55,200
Okay, bye.

271
00:11:55,600 --> 00:11:56,040
Bye.

272
00:11:57,520 --> 00:11:58,050
Xiaocen.

273
00:11:58,360 --> 00:11:59,360
What do you want to eat?

274
00:11:59,360 --> 00:11:59,960
Yuexin.

275
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:02,730
Are you going to the party tonight?

276
00:12:04,480 --> 00:12:05,240
Gathering?

277
00:12:05,840 --> 00:12:06,280
Yeah.

278
00:12:06,560 --> 00:12:07,320
There's a notice in the group chat.

279
00:12:07,320 --> 00:12:08,580
Didn't you receive it?

280
00:12:09,080 --> 00:12:10,010
What group chat?

281
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:11,640
You weren't here during military training.

282
00:12:11,640 --> 00:12:13,040
We created a class group chat then.

283
00:12:13,040 --> 00:12:14,280
I'll invite you later.

284
00:12:14,280 --> 00:12:14,800
Okay.

285
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:17,080
But

286
00:12:17,680 --> 00:12:20,280
I promised my mom to go home for dinner tonight.

287
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:23,040
Then tell your mom you're not going back tonight.

288
00:12:23,040 --> 00:12:23,480
Yeah.

289
00:12:23,960 --> 00:12:25,040
We're all going.

290
00:12:25,280 --> 00:12:27,000
And it's our first time having dinner together.

291
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:28,060
Let's go together.

292
00:12:31,240 --> 00:12:32,000
Okay.

293
00:12:36,440 --> 00:12:37,040
This is it.

294
00:12:37,560 --> 00:12:38,480
Looks pretty good.

295
00:12:38,480 --> 00:12:39,360
Smells delicious.

296
00:12:39,360 --> 00:12:39,960
Not bad.

297
00:12:40,680 --> 00:12:41,210
Let's go.

298
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:42,890
Yan Xue, what are you doing?

299
00:12:43,080 --> 00:12:43,880
Here.

300
00:12:44,320 --> 00:12:45,000
I got four kinds of dips.

301
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:45,960
Which one do you want?

302
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:46,720
Let me help you.

303
00:12:46,720 --> 00:12:47,650
I'll go in first.

304
00:12:47,880 --> 00:12:49,320
Okay, this is yours.

305
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:52,560
Here, I'll hand out the chopsticks.

306
00:12:52,560 --> 00:12:53,200
Come.

307
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:54,960
Here, take this.

308
00:12:55,360 --> 00:12:56,680
I really like that show.

309
00:12:56,680 --> 00:12:57,280
It's also about cultural relics.

310
00:12:57,280 --> 00:12:58,480
I want some. Give me a pair.

311
00:12:58,480 --> 00:12:59,480
Your chopsticks.

312
00:12:59,840 --> 00:13:01,440
Give me a pair of chopsticks.

313
00:13:02,040 --> 00:13:03,170
Yan Xue, come quick.

314
00:13:03,200 --> 00:13:04,200
The food is almost ready.

315
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:04,800
Wait a minute.

316
00:13:04,800 --> 00:13:05,720
Yan Xue, stop working.

317
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:06,520
I want some.

318
00:13:06,880 --> 00:13:07,200
Here.

319
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:07,760
Thanks.

320
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:09,720
Who doesn't have chopsticks yet?

321
00:13:09,720 --> 00:13:10,160
Here, give it to me.

322
00:13:10,160 --> 00:13:11,240
Give me another pair of chopsticks.

323
00:13:11,240 --> 00:13:12,240
Not ready yet?

324
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:13,960
No, it's not ready yet.

325
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:16,490
Wait till it's ready to put the vegetables in.

326
00:13:16,640 --> 00:13:17,640
Are we eating the vegetables now?

327
00:13:17,640 --> 00:13:18,360
Let me put it in for you.

328
00:13:18,360 --> 00:13:18,880
Thanks.

329
00:13:19,880 --> 00:13:21,040
Finally free.

330
00:13:21,320 --> 00:13:22,680
Military training was miserable.

331
00:13:22,680 --> 00:13:25,280
Getting up at 5 a.m. every day to fold the quilt.

332
00:13:25,280 --> 00:13:26,960
Had to fold it into perfect squares.

333
00:13:26,960 --> 00:13:28,090
Like blocks of tofu.

334
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:30,080
It was too hard.

335
00:13:30,120 --> 00:13:31,520
Really, I didn't fold it at all.

336
00:13:31,520 --> 00:13:32,560
I have another issue.

337
00:13:32,560 --> 00:13:34,960
I'm not used to taking showers with everyone.

338
00:13:34,960 --> 00:13:36,560
You were all tortured by the military training.

339
00:13:36,560 --> 00:13:37,080
Me?

340
00:13:37,280 --> 00:13:38,520
I was tortured by Li Zhuoting.

341
00:13:38,520 --> 00:13:38,880
Stop talking.

342
00:13:38,880 --> 00:13:40,160
Why? What happened to you two?

343
00:13:40,160 --> 00:13:41,440
What's going on with you two?

344
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:43,600
Every time the instructor brought out the food,

345
00:13:43,600 --> 00:13:44,640
as long as he was there,

346
00:13:44,640 --> 00:13:45,800
I couldn't get any meat.

347
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:46,480
Come on, eat.

348
00:13:46,480 --> 00:13:47,320
Stop talking and eat.

349
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:48,640
He grabs food so fast.

350
00:13:48,960 --> 00:13:49,760
As soon as he lunged at it,

351
00:13:49,760 --> 00:13:50,800
if you looked in the bowl,

352
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:51,800
there was only soup left.

353
00:13:51,800 --> 00:13:52,760
Don't talk nonsense.

354
00:13:52,760 --> 00:13:53,600
I'm not that exaggerating.

355
00:13:53,600 --> 00:13:54,600
Yes, you are.

356
00:13:54,640 --> 00:13:55,770
By the way, Xiaocen,

357
00:13:56,080 --> 00:13:58,810
why didn't you come to military training with us?

358
00:13:58,840 --> 00:14:00,640
My mom got me a sick leave.

359
00:14:00,880 --> 00:14:01,400
Sick leave?

360
00:14:01,400 --> 00:14:02,660
What's wrong with you?

361
00:14:03,600 --> 00:14:04,840
It's nothing serious.

362
00:14:04,840 --> 00:14:07,400
Just bad health when I was little,

363
00:14:07,400 --> 00:14:09,000
and I get heatstroke easily.

364
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:11,000
Heatstroke can get you out of military training?

365
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:12,530
Then I have heatstroke too.

366
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:14,600
Eat more.

367
00:14:14,640 --> 00:14:15,720
Okay, come on.

368
00:14:16,080 --> 00:14:18,440
Let's all toast with our drinks instead of alcohol.

369
00:14:18,440 --> 00:14:18,960
Let's propose a toast.

370
00:14:18,960 --> 00:14:19,420
Come on.

371
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:20,880
Come on. Cheers.

372
00:14:21,160 --> 00:14:23,120
We've survived the hard days of military training.

373
00:14:23,120 --> 00:14:25,080
Let's toast to our time in college.

374
00:14:25,080 --> 00:14:27,400
I hope everything goes smoothly and happily for everyone.

375
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:30,080
Most importantly, I wish for us to love and care for each other.

376
00:14:30,080 --> 00:14:30,440
Definitely.

377
00:14:30,440 --> 00:14:30,720
Okay.

378
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:31,280
Cheers.

379
00:14:31,320 --> 00:14:31,640
Come on.

380
00:14:31,640 --> 00:14:32,360
Cheers, cheers.

381
00:14:32,360 --> 00:14:32,960
Cheers, cheers.

382
00:14:32,960 --> 00:14:33,420
Come on.

383
00:14:33,480 --> 00:14:33,960
Come.

384
00:14:36,360 --> 00:14:37,760
Cheers, cheers, cheers.

385
00:14:39,040 --> 00:14:39,840
So refreshing.

386
00:14:39,840 --> 00:14:41,500
Pull your stool forward a bit.

387
00:14:41,600 --> 00:14:42,400
All right. Come on.

388
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:43,680
Let's talk about something else.

389
00:14:43,680 --> 00:14:44,810
Do you guys remember

390
00:14:45,080 --> 00:14:47,080
those late-night drills back then?

391
00:14:47,080 --> 00:14:48,080
At 1:00 a.m.

392
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:49,600
I remember.

393
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:50,360
The emergency assemblies

394
00:14:50,360 --> 00:14:51,360
almost killed me.

395
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:52,930
Why are you guys so excited?

396
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:04,400
Cheers!

397
00:15:06,560 --> 00:15:08,080
Is the pork fatty?

398
00:15:08,160 --> 00:15:09,680
Fatty!

399
00:15:09,680 --> 00:15:10,400
All right.

400
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:12,520
I've already booked the KTV.

401
00:15:12,520 --> 00:15:14,200
Watch me show off my singing skills tonight.

402
00:15:14,200 --> 00:15:15,160
Let's go!

403
00:15:15,160 --> 00:15:17,360
I'm definitely singing ten songs, I'm telling you.

404
00:15:17,360 --> 00:15:17,840
Yuexin.

405
00:15:19,560 --> 00:15:20,360
What's wrong?

406
00:15:20,560 --> 00:15:21,840
Tonight,

407
00:15:21,920 --> 00:15:23,720
my mom is waiting for me at home.

408
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:25,120
So...

409
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:28,220
Can't your mom make an exception?

410
00:15:31,080 --> 00:15:32,080
If it really doesn't work out,

411
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:33,940
we'll just have to do it next time.

412
00:15:34,560 --> 00:15:36,020
Yuexin, Yan Xue, let's go.

413
00:15:36,680 --> 00:15:37,560
Okay, coming.

414
00:15:37,760 --> 00:15:38,080
Let's go.

415
00:15:38,080 --> 00:15:39,080
I'm leaving. Bye.

416
00:15:39,760 --> 00:15:40,120
Bye.

417
00:15:40,120 --> 00:15:40,850
I'm leaving.

418
00:15:43,480 --> 00:15:44,360
Coming.

419
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:45,640
What song did you sing?

420
00:15:46,040 --> 00:15:46,640
Let's go.

421
00:15:46,640 --> 00:15:47,640
It's so slippery.

422
00:15:47,720 --> 00:15:48,250
Hurry up.

423
00:15:59,080 --> 00:16:01,360
It shows the night market is right around here.

424
00:16:01,360 --> 00:16:03,560
Really? Did you get the direction wrong?

425
00:16:03,560 --> 00:16:04,420
Hello, driver.

426
00:16:06,480 --> 00:16:09,010
I'm walking towards the pinned location now.

427
00:16:38,240 --> 00:16:39,100
Hello, driver.

428
00:16:40,440 --> 00:16:42,080
I'm on this street right now.

429
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:44,480
I don't see you.

430
00:16:47,280 --> 00:16:48,120
All right then.

431
00:16:48,120 --> 00:16:49,380
I'll call another one.

432
00:16:50,840 --> 00:16:52,240
Okay. Thank you, driver.

433
00:17:02,240 --> 00:17:03,770
Come look at the porcelain.

434
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:06,740
Fifteen for the big ones, twenty for the small ones.

435
00:17:07,560 --> 00:17:09,160
Can you make it a bit cheaper?

436
00:17:10,079 --> 00:17:10,880
Young man.

437
00:17:11,400 --> 00:17:13,359
Look at the craftsmanship on this small one.

438
00:17:13,359 --> 00:17:14,619
Look at the outlining.

439
00:17:16,520 --> 00:17:17,960
Boss, you're so nice.

440
00:17:22,839 --> 00:17:24,300
Blue and white porcelain.

441
00:17:25,119 --> 00:17:27,450
Come look at the blue and white porcelain.

442
00:17:31,320 --> 00:17:32,240
Set of cups.

443
00:17:35,080 --> 00:17:35,740
Cloud cups.

444
00:17:38,680 --> 00:17:40,360
Boss, at the price I just mentioned,

445
00:17:40,360 --> 00:17:41,220
can you sell it?

446
00:17:42,080 --> 00:17:43,680
Go ask around on this street.

447
00:18:11,600 --> 00:18:13,560
You're Xu Xiao, right?

448
00:18:14,080 --> 00:18:15,040
Hello, my name is...

449
00:18:15,040 --> 00:18:15,900
I remember you.

450
00:18:17,360 --> 00:18:19,220
During the class introductions,

451
00:18:19,600 --> 00:18:21,460
only you and I just said our names.

452
00:18:26,400 --> 00:18:27,760
Where are we?

453
00:18:27,920 --> 00:18:29,880
Why are so many people setting up stalls?

454
00:18:29,880 --> 00:18:31,010
This is Taoxichuan.

455
00:18:31,120 --> 00:18:34,120
It's the largest creative market here in Jingdezhen.

456
00:18:34,240 --> 00:18:34,680
Boss.

457
00:18:35,560 --> 00:18:36,760
Xu Xiao, you're here.

458
00:18:37,600 --> 00:18:39,530
Here are the things I found for you.

459
00:18:39,600 --> 00:18:40,200
Thank you.

460
00:18:40,960 --> 00:18:41,820
All good stuff.

461
00:18:43,960 --> 00:18:44,420
Thanks.

462
00:18:44,840 --> 00:18:45,770
You're welcome.

463
00:18:46,880 --> 00:18:47,410
How much?

464
00:18:47,600 --> 00:18:48,460
Same old price.

465
00:18:48,800 --> 00:18:49,130
Okay.

466
00:18:50,680 --> 00:18:53,080
Do you have to pay for these broken ones too?

467
00:18:53,960 --> 00:18:56,480
They are broken porcelain pieces from the Ming and Qing Dynasties.

468
00:18:56,480 --> 00:18:58,120
Then they are antiques.

469
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:00,060
Ancient porcelain

470
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:01,920
is also divided into folk kilns and official kilns.

471
00:19:01,920 --> 00:19:03,720
These are broken pieces from folk kilns,

472
00:19:03,720 --> 00:19:05,650
so the price is not very expensive.

473
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:06,920
Folk kilns.

474
00:19:07,240 --> 00:19:07,770
Let's go.

475
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:10,800
Folk kilns and official kilns.

476
00:19:21,720 --> 00:19:23,440
Miss, take a look at these porcelain decals.

477
00:19:23,440 --> 00:19:24,370
They're pretty.

478
00:19:24,840 --> 00:19:25,400
Well,

479
00:19:26,120 --> 00:19:27,400
they're closing up soon.

480
00:19:27,400 --> 00:19:28,260
I'll head back.

481
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:29,800
See you at school.

482
00:19:32,360 --> 00:19:33,280
Pay what you want.

483
00:19:33,280 --> 00:19:33,840
Buy a few.

484
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:36,280
Just don't give too little.

485
00:19:36,280 --> 00:19:36,920
Okay.

486
00:19:36,920 --> 00:19:38,320
I'll take these two then.

487
00:19:39,520 --> 00:19:40,320
Come again, beautiful.

488
00:19:40,320 --> 00:19:41,320
Okay.

489
00:19:47,160 --> 00:19:48,560
Let's walk a bit further.

490
00:19:49,280 --> 00:19:49,940
Over there.

491
00:20:08,440 --> 00:20:11,100
It's hard to get a cab here when the stalls close.

492
00:20:11,640 --> 00:20:12,640
Where do you live?

493
00:20:14,640 --> 00:20:15,640
Yuyaojing Alley.

494
00:20:16,800 --> 00:20:17,840
Just take Bus 13.

495
00:20:18,520 --> 00:20:19,120
Follow me.

496
00:21:54,960 --> 00:21:55,820
This is my stop.

497
00:22:04,880 --> 00:22:05,280
Wait.

498
00:22:08,400 --> 00:22:09,800
I'm getting off here too.

499
00:22:10,720 --> 00:22:11,250
Let's go.

500
00:22:36,840 --> 00:22:38,440
Why didn't you go to

501
00:22:38,440 --> 00:22:39,840
the class reunion today?

502
00:22:41,560 --> 00:22:42,960
I have my own things to do.

503
00:22:43,240 --> 00:22:43,960
Besides,

504
00:22:44,800 --> 00:22:46,060
we're not close enough

505
00:22:46,120 --> 00:22:47,720
that we have to eat together.

506
00:22:48,360 --> 00:22:49,960
Aren't you worried

507
00:22:50,080 --> 00:22:52,280
about not getting along with everyone?

508
00:22:53,520 --> 00:22:55,240
Or being isolated by them?

509
00:22:56,400 --> 00:22:57,080
Not at all.

510
00:22:58,440 --> 00:22:59,640
Whoever isolates me,

511
00:23:00,320 --> 00:23:01,380
I'll isolate them.

512
00:23:15,280 --> 00:23:15,800
Um.

513
00:23:17,400 --> 00:23:18,260
This is my stop.

514
00:23:18,640 --> 00:23:18,970
Okay.

515
00:23:20,400 --> 00:23:21,800
My stop is further ahead.

516
00:23:25,080 --> 00:23:26,210
I'll get going then.

517
00:23:28,680 --> 00:23:29,160
Bye.

518
00:23:30,840 --> 00:23:31,280
Bye.

519
00:24:35,520 --> 00:24:38,400
Why did I ride past my stop just to accompany her?

520
00:24:45,840 --> 00:24:46,400
And these.

521
00:24:46,400 --> 00:24:47,400
I thought we only needed clay.

522
00:24:47,400 --> 00:24:48,760
This is a full set of tools.

523
00:24:48,760 --> 00:24:49,490
So complete.

524
00:24:50,920 --> 00:24:52,000
This is so fun. Look at this.

525
00:24:52,000 --> 00:24:53,480
Hurry up and wash your hands. Come on.

526
00:24:53,480 --> 00:24:54,920
I think that looks like it.

527
00:24:54,920 --> 00:24:56,040
There's so much paint.

528
00:24:56,040 --> 00:24:57,100
Don't move around.

529
00:24:57,440 --> 00:24:58,720
Be careful.

530
00:24:58,760 --> 00:24:59,690
Wash your hands.

531
00:25:00,720 --> 00:25:02,980
I can't believe there's a name like this.

532
00:25:05,520 --> 00:25:07,580
Why are you two standing so straight?

533
00:25:07,960 --> 00:25:11,000
I heard our major's teacher is very strict.

534
00:25:11,200 --> 00:25:11,680
Yeah.

535
00:25:12,160 --> 00:25:14,400
He often scolds the students so much they are afraid to enter the classroom.

536
00:25:14,400 --> 00:25:15,130
That strict?

537
00:25:15,520 --> 00:25:16,320
Here he comes.

538
00:25:21,160 --> 00:25:23,600
Welcome to the cultural relic restoration class.

539
00:25:23,600 --> 00:25:25,800
My name is Yue Qixin.

540
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:29,360
Cultural relic restoration

541
00:25:29,360 --> 00:25:30,640
is a technique.

542
00:25:32,360 --> 00:25:32,960
Of course,

543
00:25:33,480 --> 00:25:36,800
some students already have a certain foundation.

544
00:25:36,840 --> 00:25:37,720
But I believe

545
00:25:38,120 --> 00:25:39,320
through this course,

546
00:25:39,680 --> 00:25:42,120
you should achieve one, two,

547
00:25:42,280 --> 00:25:43,960
or even more breakthroughs.

548
00:25:44,280 --> 00:25:46,840
To have a newer and

549
00:25:47,000 --> 00:25:48,920
proper understanding of relic restoration.

550
00:25:48,920 --> 00:25:50,160
Come, bring the plates over.

551
00:25:50,160 --> 00:25:51,280
Take one yourselves.

552
00:25:51,280 --> 00:25:51,760
Go.

553
00:26:07,840 --> 00:26:09,440
Those without a plate,

554
00:26:09,520 --> 00:26:11,000
find someone with a plate

555
00:26:11,040 --> 00:26:13,080
and freely form pairs.

556
00:26:13,160 --> 00:26:14,280
I don't have a plate.

557
00:26:14,280 --> 00:26:15,440
Wang Lin, let's team up.

558
00:26:15,440 --> 00:26:16,240
Absolutely.

559
00:26:16,760 --> 00:26:17,090
Okay.

560
00:26:17,280 --> 00:26:18,400
Let's team up.

561
00:26:18,720 --> 00:26:20,120
What should we do now?

562
00:26:20,120 --> 00:26:21,120
I don't know.

563
00:26:22,240 --> 00:26:23,700
What are we supposed to do?

564
00:26:24,560 --> 00:26:25,280
We're a team.

565
00:26:25,280 --> 00:26:25,720
Okay.

566
00:26:26,520 --> 00:26:27,240
This looks really nice.

567
00:26:27,240 --> 00:26:28,080
I don't really like this pattern.

568
00:26:28,080 --> 00:26:28,740
Me neither.

569
00:26:28,920 --> 00:26:30,360
This is so beautiful.

570
00:26:31,080 --> 00:26:32,280
I'll team up with you.

571
00:26:34,000 --> 00:26:34,720
Is that okay?
